Face Recognition Tele Bot
Overview
The Face Recognition Tele Bot is a Telegram bot designed for face recognition using Python and popular libraries like OpenCV and dlib. The bot allows users to upload images or provide URLs of images to perform face recognition. The underlying face recognition is powered by the dlib library, known for its accuracy in face detection and recognition tasks.

Features
Face Recognition: The bot uses the dlib library to detect and recognize faces in images.
Telegram Integration: Interact with the bot through Telegram, making it easy to use and accessible to a wide audience.
Image Upload and URL Support: Users can upload images or provide image URLs for face recognition.
Getting Started
Prerequisites
Python 3.x
Telegram Bot Token (Get one by talking to BotFather)
Installation
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/mkghgit/face_recognition_tele_bot.git
cd face_recognition_tele_bot
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Set up your Telegram Bot Token:

Obtain a token from BotFather.

Create a file named .env in the project root and add your token:

Run the bot:

bash
Copy code
python bot.py
Open Telegram and start a chat with your bot.

Send an image or provide an image URL to the bot to perform face recognition.
